Awards

2023 All-American

2023 NCAA qualifier, finalist

2023 NCAA regional champion

2023 USFCA all-region first team

2022 All-American

2022 NCAA qualifier, semifinalist

2022 second-team All-Ivy

2022 NCAA regional champion

2020 Olympian, individual quarterfinalist and finishing eighth with the Egyptian foil team

2016 Olympian, finishing seventh with the Egyptian foil team

2019 All-American

2019 NCAA qualifier, finishing sixth

2019 second-team All-Ivy

At Princeton

2022-23

NCAA runner-up, earning All-American honors ... NCAA Regional champion ... went 7-2 at the Penn Elite Invitational and 10-2 at the Sacred Heart Duals.

2021-22

NCAA semifinalist ... second-team All-Ivy ... NCAA Mid-Atlantic/South regional champion ... opened the season with an 18-0 finish at the Drew Duals before going 11-1 at the Sacred Heart Duals and 3-0 at the Philadelphia Invitational ... went 5-7 at the Ivy round-robins ... earned the top seed after pool competition at the NCAA Championships, edged by eventual champ Ashton Daniel of Columbia 15-14 in the semifinals.

2020-21

Season canceled due to COVID-19.

2019-20

Took the year off from collegiate competition.

2018-19

All-America, finishing sixth at the NCAA Championships ... second-team All-Ivy League, going 10-5 at the Ivy League round-robins ... NCAA regional runner-up ... went at 9-3 at Ohio State and 7-1 at Sacred Heart.

Before Princeton: Competed with the Egyptian men's foil team at the 2016 Olympics in Brazil ... as of February 2018, ranked No. 6 in the FIE Junior World Rankings ... in 2017, won two gold medals at the cadet and junior African Championships in CÃ´te d'Ivoire ... won bronze at the U20 Fencing World Cup in 2017 ... competed with the Salle Mauro fencing club.

Personal: Son of Maher Hamza and Noura Younis ... has a sister, Malak ... majoring in mechanical and aerospace engineering.
